EPL: Solskjaer boosted by return of three Man Utd senior players ahead of Everton clash Manchester United manager, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, has been handed a huge injury boost, with the return of three senior stars ahead of the festive fixtures. The Red Devils host Everton at Old Trafford on Sunday. United then play Watford, Newcastle, Burnley and Arsenal over the Christmas and New Year period. Speaking to the media on Friday, Solskjaer has revealed that Paul Pogba, Eric Bailly and Timothy Fosu-Mensah, are set to return to training by next week. “Next week Eric will start training, Tim will start training. “Paul will probably start training with us next week properly so let’s see,” Solskjaer said. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.